quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  42,52,"And thus have We revealed a spirit to you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>by Our command. You<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>did not know what the Scripture was nor what faith was, but We made it a light with which We guide whomever We will of Our servants. And most surely, you guide to a straight path—"
  42,53,"the path of Allah to whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth. Undoubtedly, to Allah are destined all commands."
  43,1,"Ha Mīm."
  43,2,"By the Evident Scripture,"
  43,3,"indeed, We made it an Arabic Recital{1}, that you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>may reason.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  43,4,"And indeed, it is with Us in the Source of Scriptures, all-high, all-wise."
  43,5,"So shall We ignore reminding you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>, <span class=""h"">for having been<sup foot_note=""81094"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>an extremist people?"
  43,6,"And how many a prophet did We send to the ancients!"
  43,7,"Yet not a prophet came to them but that they used to ridicule him."
  43,8,"Thus We annihilated people more powerful than them, and so the example of the ancients has passed away."
  43,9,"And were you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>to ask them, “Who created the heavens and the earth?” They would say, “The Almighty, the All-Knowing created them.”"
  43,10,"He Who made the earth a <span class=""h"">cradle<sup foot_note=""81095"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span> for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>and traced in it ways for you, that you may be guided."
